      <stringProp name="TestPlan.comments">JMeter - How to do Remote Testing
How to do Distributed Testing
How to create Master Slave


Step 1 : SetUp Master
   added remote systemâ€™s ip in jmeter.properties

Step 2 : create keystore file
    run create-rmi-keystore.bat / create-rmi-keystore.sh
   name : rmi (Necessary Input)
   password : changeit (If Asks For It, USe This Default Passohrase)

Step 3 : run jmeter-server file on slave (remote) system

Step 4 : Run and Validate
    GUI : run -&gt; Remote Start 
    and 
    Commandline : Navigate To Jmeter Bin Directory And Type This Following  jmeter -n -t &quot;Location Of JMX File &quot; -l &quot;Log Saved File Location&quot; -R [Remote HOst IP Address] 
    And Hit Enter
  

Helpful Tips:

 - all systems (master and slaves) have same ver of JMeter
 - all systems have java (preferably same ver)
 - all systems can connect to each other (are in same subnet)

 - no need to copy jmeter script (jmx) to slave systems

 - If you want to have 100 users and using  2 slaves. Give no as 50</stringProp>
